@yashypn0 All modern NAND is optimized for sequential writes...moving fat files around.

Optane was wild because it was designed for small, random reads/writes.  More like system RAM.

It is *still* often 10x faster than the best SSDs you can currently buy. https://t.co/ouL7ZuofFu

